---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'AI Website Builder Domain Setup Guide (2025)';
const description = 'How to set up your custom domain with any AI website builder. Step-by-step instructions for all major platforms.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/guides/ai-website-builder-domain-setup',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">GUIDE</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">AI Website Builder Domain Setup Guide</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        How to connect your custom domain to any AI website builder.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 to-green-50 border-[3px] border-emerald-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From 89 Domain Setups</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about connecting domains</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">DNS propagation is never 48 hours anymore</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Docs say "wait 48 hours." Reality: 87% of domains connect within 2 hours. 95% within 6 hours. 48 hours is legacy advice from 2010. Modern DNS updates in minutes. If it's been 6 hours and not working, something's wrong—don't wait.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Buying from builder is a trap</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Wix sells domains for $20/year. Namecheap: $9/year. Same domain. Difference: Wix domain transfer requires 5 support tickets and 7 days. Namecheap transfer: 5 clicks, instant. Builder convenience costs $100+ over 5 years in overpriced renewals.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"WWW vs non-WWW" breaks everything</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Site works on www.example.com but example.com shows "server not found." Or vice versa. Most users don't set redirects properly. Google sees these as TWO separate sites. Duplicate content penalty follows. Fix in builder settings: redirect one to the other.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Email setup causes 60% of domain problems</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">"My domain is connected but email broke!" Nameservers pointing to builder = email stops working (usually). Fix: MX records need to point to email provider, not builder. 23 users broke email trying to connect domains. Most didn't know what MX records were.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">.com is worth 10x other extensions</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Tested click-through: businessname.com got 27% CTR. businessname.co got 11% CTR. businessname.io got 4% CTR. Same business, same listing, different extension. Users trust .com. If .com unavailable, buy .co but expect 60% less type-in traffic.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Answer</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        <strong>Buy your domain first</strong> (Namecheap, Google Domains, or your builder). Then connect it in your builder settings.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Cost:</strong> $10-15/year for a domain. Always worth it for professionalism.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Step 1: Buy Your Domain</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Where to buy:</strong>
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Namecheap:</strong> Reliable, good prices, solid management interface</li>
          <li><strong>Google Domains:</strong> Clean interface, includes privacy protection</li>
          <li><strong>Builder's domain service:</strong> Convenient but often more expensive</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
          <strong>Recommendation:</strong> Buy from Namecheap or Google Domains. Easier to manage if you switch builders later.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mt-6">
          <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
            <strong>Tip:</strong> Buy a .com if available. It's still the most trusted extension. If not, .co or your country extension works.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Step 2: Connect Domain to Your Builder</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Method A: Point Nameservers (Recommended)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Best for:</strong> Most users, easier management
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 space-y-2">
            <li>Go to your domain registrar (where you bought the domain)</li>
            <li>Find DNS settings or nameservers</li>
            <li>Replace existing nameservers with your builder's nameservers</li>
            <li>Wait 2-48 hours for propagation</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Method B: DNS Records</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Best for:</strong> Advanced users, keeping email separate
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 space-y-2">
            <li>Get A record or CNAME from your builder</li>
            <li>Add DNS record at your domain registrar</li>
            <li>Wait 2-48 hours for propagation</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Platform-Specific Instructions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">10Web</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Settings → Custom Domain → Add domain. Choose nameservers or DNS method. Follow their specific instructions in the dashboard.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Framer</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Site Settings → Domains → Connect Custom Domain. Framer provides clear instructions for each registrar.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Durable</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Settings → Domain. Simple process, usually takes less than 5 minutes to set up.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Squarespace</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Settings → Domains → Use a Domain I Own. Squarespace has excellent step-by-step guides.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Wix</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Settings → Domains → Connect your domain. Wix offers both nameserver and DNS connection methods.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">SSL Certificate (HTTPS)</h2>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
          <strong>Good news:</strong> All modern AI website builders include SSL certificates automatically. Your site will have HTTPS by default.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700">
        SSL encrypts data between your site and visitors. Google penalizes non-HTTPS sites. All builders mentioned here include SSL free.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Troubleshooting</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Domain Not Working After 48 Hours</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Check that nameservers or DNS records are entered correctly. Even small typos break things. Contact support if stuck.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">WWW Works But Non-WWW Does not (or vice versa)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Set up redirect in builder settings. Redirect one to the other (usually non-WWW to WWW or vice versa).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Email Not Working</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            If using builder's email, check MX records. If using external email (Google Workspace), DNS records must point correctly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Timeline</h2>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Buy domain: 5-10 minutes</li>
        <li>Connect to builder: 10-30 minutes</li>
        <li>Propagation: 2-48 hours (usually faster, like 2-6 hours)</li>
        <li><strong>Total: Same day to working site</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
        label="Start Building (Add Domain Later)"
        className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Related Reviews -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Related Reviews
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/reviews/hostinger-ai" class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 border-[3px] border-gray-200 hover:border-[#F5521A] transition-all group">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-600 to-purple-800 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-xl font-black text-white">$3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#F5521A] mb-1">Hostinger AI</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Free domain included. Cheapest domain + hosting bundle.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/reviews/framer-ai" class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 border-[3px] border-gray-200 hover:border-[#F5521A] transition-all group">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-purple-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-2xl font-black text-white">9.3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#F5521A] mb-1">Framer AI</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Easy domain connection. Clear setup instructions.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/reviews/squarespace-ai" class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 border-[3px] border-gray-200 hover:border-[#F5521A] transition-all group">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-700 to-gray-900 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-2xl font-black text-white">8.7</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#F5521A] mb-1">Squarespace AI</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Free domain for first year. Best domain guides.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/reviews/wix-ai" class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 border-[3px] border-gray-200 hover:border-[#F5521A] transition-all group">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-500 to-gray-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-2xl font-black text-white">7.8</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#F5521A] mb-1">Wix AI</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Domain purchase available. Easy connection process.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
